<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="3">

  <Content>
    <Paragraph Type="Shot">
      <Text>fade iN:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Shot">
      <Text>BLACK SCREEN.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We hear...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>...the SCAMPER of FOOTSTEPS SHUFFLE through LEAVES...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>...HEAVY BREATHING...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>...POLICE SIRENS GROW LOUDER and LOUDER...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Dissolve to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>ext. apartment complex Courtyard - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>FLASH ON EL, a young mute Latina crouched in the bushes; alert next to her stands ALBIE on all paws, a companion and a dog.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SIRENS blare, the sound is overwhelming. The LIGHTS from the SIRENS beat against El and Albie’s faces.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both watch in horror as the police try and summon the inhabitant of the apartment on the second floor across and above from where they hide.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Color="#FFFF00000000" Length="3/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>int. Yellow corvette trunk - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHEEN, a naked young adult Latina, lies slack jawed in the trunk of a YELLOW CORVETTE covered in blood, her neck black and bruised; she’s tied up hog style and most importantly, </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">she‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> dead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Shot">
      <Text>PULL BACK to REVEAL:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The SHADOW of a MAN in head to toe BIKER GEAR looming over the trunk, his hand on the hood. He SLAMS the trunk closed</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>FLASH Cut:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>ext. apartment complex Courtyard - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSER on El and Albie. OFF SCREEN we hear the sound of a DOOR being SLAMMED OPEN.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">int.</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">Sheen‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> bathroom - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen, same one as before, lies slack jawed on the toilet, arms sliced not sideways for attention but longways for results.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON a NAIL POLISHED HAND WRITING a SUICIDE NOTE with </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Sheen‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> DEAD and HEAVY ARM.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CAMERA PULLS BACK revealing the backside of a woman in RED DRESS as she bends down to grab </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Sheen‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> legs and then begins to drag her dead body off the toilet, onto the floor, and out of the bathroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>FLASH Cut:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">ext</Text>
      <Text>. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">apartment</Text>
      <Text> complex</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Fear grips El, El grips Albie; their bodies now closer together than just moments before. OFF SCREEN the BLARING of more SIRENS approach.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">cut</Text>
      <Text> to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">int.</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">Sheen‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> apartment / bedroom - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen, slumped over her bed, nose and mouth bloodied; her hands clutch her face, a foaming drink fizzles spilt on the carpet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen twitches and contorts.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Sheen‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> breath runs out and she dies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The SHADOW of a NAKED MAN lingers in the background.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CUT TO a CLOSE OVER the SHOULDER of the NAKED MAN, revealing his BALD HEAD.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>FLASH Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">ext</Text>
      <Text>. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">apartment</Text>
      <Text> complex - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>EXTREME CLOSE UP on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">El‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> face, tears welling in her eyes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">dissolve</Text>
      <Text> to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. El‚Äôs APARTMENT - MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>FLASH ON El, sitting on the couch across from her adopted parents, SANDRA and DAVE, sitting on different chairs, hands loosely clasped. Sandra, uncomfortable, readjusts herself in her seat, letting go of </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Dave‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They take a collective deep breath before we‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>CUT TO:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / El‚Äôs bedroom - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">El‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> alarm fires off at 6:00am, snoozed by a disembodied hand, then blares once more at 6:07am.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El propels herself out of bed after a grimace and some hesitance. She knows if </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">it‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> not going to be now it‚Äôs going to be never.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="28 3/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARB"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CANVAS‚Äô POV"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DAVE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUGH"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JEANNIE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SANDRA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. El‚Äôs apartment / bathroom - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">El‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> in the bathroom, brushing her teeth, and taking care of other morning routines a preteen might embark upon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El checks her pretty popular blog, reviews new notifications (and responds to a few), she writes a good morning post.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El reviews </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">MIA‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> blog. MIA is a bully from </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">El‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> high school, and posts a ton of selfies and gets a lot of comments from boys much to El‚Äôs chagrin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra knocks on the bathroom door, her hair up on her head in a towel, El unlocks the door and Sandra pops her head in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hands her a brush.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Dave got fired‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>‚ÄîDave, got let go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Dave got let go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">I‚Äôm</Text>
      <Text> getting unemployment. It is different and worth noting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.</Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">s.</Text>
      <Text>)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yes, of course, I know that. I don‚Äôt see why its important for the sake of this conversation though.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They‚Äôre very different things. One implies that I was not a good worker, and the other implies the company has fallen on hard times.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dear, pedantic is when someone is annoying about minor details of a</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>story, details that don‚Äôt really change the fact of the matter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She knows what pedantic means. She is 14. There‚Äôs also a difference between being annoying about a detail and being concerned with conveying the whole truth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I was talking to you, Dave. El, point is: money is a bit tight around here at the moment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We are not poor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Not poor, or broke, or in danger of getting kicked out or anything of that sort of serious nature. We‚Äôre letting you know because we want to treat you like an adult.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Its just that money is going to be tight until I find work again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>This is not why we sat you down to talk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yeah, yeah. The point is‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The point is we are gonna need some help around here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Nothing back breaking, or anything of the sort.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>No, of course not. Just a little help here and little help there. You really are already carrying a lot of your own weight. We just need a little extra help.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / hallway - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Dave have an awkward encounter in the hallway, with low lighting. Without making eye contact one tries to pass by moving to the right, the other also tries to move right‚Äîthen both to the left, and so on and so on until one finally passes the other.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Nothing we wouldn‚Äôt ask of our own daughter. Which is what we consider you, sweetie. One of us. And when a family is hurting, we need to watch out for each other.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. El‚Äôs apartment / El‚Äôs bedroom - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>In El‚Äôs room, there is a canvas with an oil painting she left up from the night before, it is dark, muddy, grey ‚Äî an abstract form of a face‚Äôs profile could be made out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El gives it a look over before dipping a new brush into paint, she adds one stroke.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Then snaps a picture of it with her cellphone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You are like our own daughter. It‚Äôs just that going school shopping every few months for new clothes, the daily bus fare, the money everyday for school lunch. It‚Äôs just that it‚Äôs getting a little too tight to squeeze. And also, we think working is a very, very important character building activity. Very important!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>My grandpa used to make my dad dig holes in the backyard. Told him that blisters were the sign of a man. I had a job since I was ten helping my dad empty septic tanks back up north in Jersey. We‚Äôre not asking for you to empty septic tanks, no siree‚Äîwouldn‚Äôt wish that job on my worst enemy‚Äîalso Florida doesn‚Äôt have septic tanks, I don‚Äôt think‚Ä¶</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El washes the newly dirtied paint brush in the sink before laying it out next to the sink on some paper towels to dry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El pops two waffles into the toaster.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El pulls up the photo of her painting on her computer, and starts editing it at the kitchen table, waiting for the toaster.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave joins her at the kitchen table with a bowl of cereal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And I worked for my daddy too, helping him type up his psych notes at the end of the day and file them by color coding them. My mom actually trained me to type at six years old. The main idea here is that we need some help around here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We made a list of some potential jobs that a 14 year old girl with your temperament might be able to handle. Just a few quick ideas to throw your way.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yes, a few things we think might suit you nicely and not stress your poor self too hard with. Like I said, just some things for some pocket change so you can treat yourself when you want that extra scoop of ice cream. Buy some candy on the way home from school, or get two cookies instead of one. This extra help is just for you. Just for you to take care of yourself. We will never ask for a dime.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / El‚Äôs bedroom - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El rushes to grab a pair of shoes from her closet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>After lacing up her shoes, El walks over to her bedside table drawer, opens it, and pulls out a journal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She opens the journal and the journal opens immediately to the page where El keeps a picture of her mother.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She stares at it for a few beats before closing the journal and putting it back in its rightful place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El moves over to her window, grabs a brush from her desk and begins brushing her hair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She peaks out through the blinds of the window. Her bedroom overlooks the parking lot, and she spies GARY, late 30‚Äôs - early 40‚Äôs, talking to a handful of his migrant workers. After some deliberating, a few get into his pickup, a few get into their own beat up car, and both vehicles take off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Almost at the same moment, a YELLOW CORVETTE with a loud rumbling exhaust pulls into the parking lot, Sheen gets out of the car and heads up a flight of stairs, the YELLOW CORVETTE pulls out of the lot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We all need to learn how to take care of ourselves, anyway.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Its the most important lesson anyone could learn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>So best to learn it early!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave, do you have the list?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Right here. Wait.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INT. El‚Äôs APARTMENT / LIVING ROOM - MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CAMERA FRAMES El, Sandra, and Dave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CAMERA SUPER SLOWLY ZOOMS onto El‚Äôs FACE until we reach an EXTREME CLOSEUP as the scene plays out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave reaches into his pockets to dig out the note, it takes him a minute, and a few tries, but he successfully finds the list, looks at it for a moment about to read it, and then hands it to Sandra.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Okay, so this one is a cool one. A playmate slash babysitter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Or! We were thinking maybe bagging groceries at Publix. And there‚Äôs a Publix between your school and our apartment. And I bet you‚Äôll not only make an hourly wage, but if you help some of the old folks out of the door and into their car they might hand you an extra buck or two. Perfect, right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Oh, here‚Äôs a great one, especially because you are so super smart. A math tutor for some public school kids? You‚Äôve always been really strong at math, that is for sure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And I‚Äôve never been good in math, not my whole life, and boy, would‚Äôve I killed for a sweet, cute tutor like yourself when I was a young kid. Not that I‚Äôm too old now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El‚Äôs lack of reaction to their suggestions causes Sandra and Dave to panic.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra reviews the entirety of the list, stammers, and then says:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Um, a lot of our neighbors have pets, maybe a dog walker?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El‚Äôs face lights up at this suggestion. She nods her head, and her adopted parents are relieved.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El reaches into her pocket and pulls out a deck of cards wrapped in a rubber band.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON El thumbing through the cards. The cards, on one side appear as normal playing cards, on the other side are hand written phrases in marker.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hands Dave one of the cards, and before even looking at what the card says, he hands the card right to Sandra.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON Sandra‚ÄôS HAND HOLDING the CARD in the foreground over El‚Äôs out of focus face in the background.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HANDWRITING READS: ‚ÄúSounds Good!‚Äù (A smiley face is drawn underneath the handwriting).</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra‚Äôs HAND pulls out of frame, and El‚Äôs smiling face comes into focus.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. high school / courtyard - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>All around high school teens are engaged in their lunch period: selfie slash video taking, instant messaging, and other forms of electronic distractions. This is high school, kids are smoking cigarettes, boys and girls flirt. Boys are playing handball, some of the kids are shirtless with their tee tucked into their back pocket.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CAMERA lingers on the children for awhile, before PULLING BACK to reveal:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, distant from the others, sitting on a bench near the opposite end of the playground where the chaos of recess unfolds, she is munching on a snack, laptop in her lap, and earbuds in her ears.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON her laptop: she builds a flyer offering her dog walking services.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A message pings on her screen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CUT TO a group of girls in the distance crowded around one particular girl‚Äôs phone. They are laughing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on MIA amongst the group of girls, her the ringleader.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El opens the message on her computer and it is from the group of girls, they are taunting her. It is a message presented as faux friendliness, but El‚Äôs reaction to their message makes it clear that this is anything but friendly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El‚Äôs disgusted as another barrage of messages proceed to unfurl, and she quickly ignores the messages.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. military base - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A group of live and tied female bodies are lined up against a cement wall, their heads concealed by burlap sacks, the sacks tied around their throats with yarn tied into exaggerated red bows like giant Christmas presents.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CAMERA PULLS BACK to REVEAL El in boots and military garb, her arm cocked behind her back gripping a pistol.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El paces to and fro pivoting on her heels, pauses center aligned in the FRAME, pulls the pistol from behind her back, takes a moment to aim and fires.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The girls on the wall scream upon hearing the first round sound off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El unloads the entire clip of the pistol into their bodies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON the girls as they die in slow motion.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El lifts the smoking barrel to her lip and blows like a real cowgirl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. high school / courtyard - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She continues to multitask her projects before once again being pinged by the girls‚Äîthis time, however, its a picture of her from the girls perspective, and they are taunting her even further.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El closes her laptop, wraps up her earbuds, and packs up her belongings into her backpack.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>In the distance the group of girls draw near.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, in no rush, walks off, leaving the school grounds, and heads down the sidewalk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ext. street - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El meanders down the street of her neighborhood.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She window shops, snapping photos of some things she may want in the future.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El adds to her list of ‚ÄòFuture Endeavors Post Florida‚Äô the hopes of owning her own pair of faux leather pants and maybe a fur coat when she moves away from Florida.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>EXT. Bakery - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El stops at the local bakery and lingers outside of the entrance.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>There is a customer inside, wrapping up her order, so El hangs back and allows for the customer to finish her order before she proceeds inside.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We can over hear the conversation between the BAKER and CUSTOMER.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Customer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Okay, you convinced me. One pound of chocolate covered strawberries.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Baker</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You‚Äôre not going to regret it. I promise.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Customer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yeah, well, if my husband asks, you pulled my arm.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Baker</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>If your husband tries these strawberries he ain‚Äôt gonna be asking who pulled which arm to deliver them to his belly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Customer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>His big, and getting bigger belly. And from your mouth to God‚Äôs ears.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>baker</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And dear, do His ear‚Äôs hear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>customer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Me and Harry drove by this church off Hypoluxo on the way to chemo the other day. It has those beautiful bells swinging from the steeple up above, you ever see them?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Baker</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yes, they don‚Äôt work‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Customer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>But they sure look nice!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Baker</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>God bless you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Customer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And you as well, dear. Have a happy holiday. See you soon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CUSTOMER heads out of the shop and walks past El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Bakery - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Once the CUSTOMER leaves the bakery, El enters the bakery, behind the counter is SHARON. SHARON is a single, middle aged woman, religious, and an avid plant collector (we know this because the BAKERY is adorned with an overwhelming amount of plants and flowers).</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El! You‚Äôre early, yet, perfect time! You just missed a whole heck of a crowd. Bingo let out down the block, and all the ladies walked on down here for ‚Äútheir exercise‚Äù and ate a load of cannoli. One of them broke from the pack and had one vanilla gingerbread man and one chocolate gingerbread man‚Äîthe whole crew gave her hell for it. Those old birds!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El walks up to the counter, and SHARON hands her a prepackaged box of baked goods.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El opens the ribbon surrounding the box, takes out a baked good and munches on it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (cont‚Äôd)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I didn‚Äôt tie the ribbon tight this time. I packed some rainbow cookies for Sandra. Send your mom my regards.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El‚Äôs face distorts quickly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>sharon (cont‚Äôd)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Right, not your mom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El waves behind a munching mouth and begins to leave the bakery. She takes a step towards the door between each munch and each word that SHARON offers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (cont‚Äôd)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Also, mass this Sunday morning, if you‚Äôd like. The Father keeps asking about you. He says, where is that sweet young girl you used to bring all the time. El, I promise you, he will change your life. It‚Äôs important to have an ear of the man who has the ear of God. And never let the Devil grab hold of you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Church - MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHARON kneels at the altar dressed in robes, light pours through the stained glass. She speaks in tongues, body contorting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A priest stands before her, consecrating her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Bakery - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, laughs, then waves once again, this time more certainly and affirmatively, before slipping out the front door, giggling further.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. STREET - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen passes by El walking down the street.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El eyes kept on the ground as she approaches Sheen, sneaks a glance up at Sheen, looking worse for wear, right before passing one another.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El waits for a few seconds, then turns and watches Sheen walk, and falter in her heels, before entering into the bakery.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Public transportation / bus - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El works again on her computer, the chaos of the bus surrounds her, and she is able to ignore it. She plays around with fonts and sizes of shapes on her flyer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She makes a short list of places to post the flyers around.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Listening to music, and visibly flustered, she closes her laptop, places it into her backpack, and takes out a notepad before staring out the bus window, watching traffic and taking in the ambiance of the environment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El scans the bus, then begins to sketch one of the people on the bus. She draws a quick, and rough outline, before layering on detail. She is talented.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The bus halts to a stop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El watches those who get on the bus, she notices HUGH walk onto the bus. HUGH is one of El‚Äôs neighbors; he is in his 70‚Äôs, retired, Jewish, and from New York. His hands are filled with plastic grocery bags from PUBLIX and he struggles to find the change in his pocket to pay for the bus fare.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>After it takes too long, and after HUGH assures the bus driver he has all the money and just needs to dig for it, the driver puts the bus back in motion, making HUGH wobble and almost lose balance before regaining control and continuing the change hunt.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH finishes paying his fare, and walks to find a seat. He finds one between to other bus patrons, sits in it, adjusts himself, before making eye contact with El, eye contact that she tries to evade, but once the eye contact is made there is no turning back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH beckons El over to a seat near him with a big smile.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HUGH</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>El! El! Come sit down over here, come give an old man a hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El gets up with only minor hesitation and makes her way over to HUGH on the bus. Her posture defeated: shoulders slumped.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to one of the patrons next to him)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Could you change your seat?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The patron disturbed, hesitates, huffs, then stands up to make room for El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El plops down right next to HUGH after he moves some of his grocery bags. They are sitting next to one another, and as HUGH begins to rant, no eye contact is made.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barbra, keeps telling me to get more exercise, to at least go for a walk around the block‚Äîshe keeps saying how Publix is just around the corner and that my body could use the movement. Mind you, I have a bad knee, completely metal, well, mostly metal, now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. street - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH, arms cocked on both sides of his body, power walks down the street, one mechanical leg propelling him forward, moving robot-like, the other leg dragging behind weakened and defeated.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH rushes through town, the background a blur.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">HUGH‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> robot leg out performs the rest of his body, and he grows tired, weak, then terrified. He begins to silently scream asking for the propulsion of the leg to stop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh (CONT'D) (o.</Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">s.</Text>
      <Text>)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>So, just to shut her up, I go for </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">walks‚Äîand</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">don‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> ever tell her this, but I do enjoy </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">them‚Äîits</Text>
      <Text> nice to get some sun on your skin when </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">you‚Äôre</Text>
      <Text> getting </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">old‚Äîbut</Text>
      <Text> how old do you have to get before you get to make decisions all on your </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">own‚Äîabout</Text>
      <Text> time I mind me and she minds </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">her‚Äîlove</Text>
      <Text> of my life, she </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">is‚Äîbut</Text>
      <Text> a real pain in the </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">ass‚Äîso</Text>
      <Text> I go on these walks, and where am I gonna walk to? </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">There‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> no OBT around here, the parks are unbearable and hot. What, should I just go bake in the sun so I could dry up and rot with cancer?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">int.</Text>
      <Text> Supermarket - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH wanders around the supermarket, offending everyone. Those he offends react in exaggerated manners. Their irritation propels them from </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">HUGH‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> space like batteries of the same charge.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El is also in the supermarket running from HUGH.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El ducks into an aisle of health food thinking she is safe from the oppression of </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">HUGH‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> rant.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>On the opposite end of the aisle, El notices the group of her bullies walking towards her. They all have weapons of destruction in their hands and blood in their eyes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El darts from the aisle to once again find HUGH, now an infectious disease of a human being, his orifices ooze with glowing goo.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The sight of HUGH terrifies everyone who comes into contact with him. Anyone in the supermarket who spots him, turns and runs in fear of being infected by his terrible virus.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, the BULLIES, and the rest of the CROWD run in fear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh (cont‚Äôd) (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>So, of course, I end up at the supermarket. Their lox are terrible by the way, I don‚Äôt know what they do to their fish down here, but nothing like the delis home. I‚Äôm walking and I end up at the market and you know, of course, I‚Äôm just browsing to kill some time to keep Barb happy, but this walk needs to be fruitful, so I make a lap, pick up a basket, and before you know it the basket is fulled to the brim. You know, I don‚Äôt even comprehend why they use those damned baskets cause you can‚Äôt even fit a gallon of milk and a bottle of soda in their without breaking your arm. So I‚Äôm on my third lap now, and I got my basket in the wagon, and I‚Äôm hungry from my walk so my eyes are of course bigger than my stomach ends up being. I told that nice colored boy behind the counter to slice the ham paper thin, and he</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>let me try some, and it was pretty pretty thin, but maybe not thin enough. I didn‚Äôt want to push it though. Figured, I didn‚Äôt want to be thought of as picky. Though, I</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>do believe it‚Äôs important to get what I paid for, especially at these prices. I‚Äôm not complaining though. I can‚Äôt wait to get home and make a nice ham sandwich with spicy mustard, have a side of some pickles and potato chips. And of course I got Barb some liverwurst. She would have my head, and some of my other parts too, if I come home with cold cuts and not liverwurst. Liverwurst sliced nice and thick. Very thick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Barb and Hugh‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH, on his hands and knees, eats his ham sandwich from the dog bowl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB and HUGH‚Äôs dog, MADISON, sits in HUGH‚Äôs seat at the dinner table across from BARB eating her dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB, equipped with a shit eating grin, leans over to wipe MADISON‚Äôs mouth with fine napkin wear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh (cont‚Äôd) (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What‚Äôs funny is both her and and the dog eat it. She shoves the dogs seizure medication into it, folds it up, and the damned dog gobbles it up. Dumb dog.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Barb and Hugh‚Äôs apartment / bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH lies paraplegic in bed. He falls asleep, the room grows dark.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A CRACK OF LIGHT BREAKS THE DARKNESS. BARB‚Äôs a shadow, and she sneaks over to HUGH lying in bed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON HUGH‚Äôs SLEEPING face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BARB‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> SHADOW engulfs </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">HUGH‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> FACE, pillow in her hand, then she SLAMS and HOLDS the pillow over HUGH‚Äôs FACE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH awakens and struggles with as much might as a old paraplegic might be able summon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(cont‚Äôd</Text>
      <Text>) (o.s)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>When she starts shoving my medicine in liverwurst is when I told her she should kill me, just pull the plug, put the pillow over my head, whatever the case. I </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">don‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> wanna be a crippled who </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">can‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> chew his own food and has to eat goddamned dog food. I have dignity. You heard that right, this old fart still has his dignity in tact! She wants to live to her last breath though. Keep her alive. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">That‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> what she says anyway. And never let anyone cut into her or take any kidneys or livers. She </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">don‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> want her liver to end up in a gay. And she </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">don‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> want to end up in the ground neither. She said she wants to get cooked up, turned to ash, and I gotta keep her in the house. I </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">don‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> know that seems kinda spooky to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">int.</Text>
      <Text> Barb and </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Hugh‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> apartment / kitchen - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH sits at the kitchen table with a steak dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BARB‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> ASHES lie in an URN on the middle of the table. The lid of the URN lifts up and down all on its own, and </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">BARB‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> voice literally puffs out in clouds of text nagging HUGH as he attempts to swallow his dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH stands from his dinner, picks up the URN, and flings the URN against the wall.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The URN smashes and powder disperses into the air, the powder grows thicker and thicker until the room is filled.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH chokes on the smoke, falls to his knees, and dies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(cont‚Äôd</Text>
      <Text>) (o.</Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">s.</Text>
      <Text>)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Having your dead wife just sitting on the kitchen table while </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">you‚Äôre</Text>
      <Text> reading the paper and drinking coffee.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ext. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">street</Text>
      <Text> - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and HUGH walk down the street, their apartment complex in sight. El holds all of the bags, HUGH relinquishing the workload. The conversation, if it could be called that, picks up seamlessly as if the rant has never paused or ended.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The buses are just nothing like they are back home. Let me tell you something, no where in the world do they do transport like they do in New York City. No where, not the filthy </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Japs</Text>
      <Text>, not the fancy British, not those damned holier than thou Californians with all their traffic. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">That‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> not to say that we </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">don‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> get a lot of traffic, especially when those fair-weather Floridians come and go with the seasons. But New </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">York‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> subways </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">system‚ÄîIt‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> flawless. Besides the rats. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Korean‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">didn‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> even have trains when I was shipped off there. Savages. You know, when my kids were young, I worked hard, very hard, and I swore when Susie was born that </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">I‚Äôd</Text>
      <Text> be able to afford to take them to Disney at least once a year.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ext. barb and Hugh‚Äôs apartment - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB and HUGH‚Äôs apartment door opens and BARB steps out from overhearing the booming voice of her husband HUGH in the courtyard. BARB is also in her 70s, and is wearing one of those dresses that could also pass for a nightgown, she is also wearing high white socks and slip on sandals.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Barb and Hugh‚Äôs apartment - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB rushes to the kitchen table to grab her pocketbook.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She fumbles through it to grab lipstick, quickly applies the lipstick in the mirror by the front door, and fixes up her hair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She rummages through her purse for loose change. After finding a handful of change from the bottom of the purse, she dumps the quarters, and saves a few nickels in her palm.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. barb and Hugh‚Äôs apartment - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB opens the door to their apartment again in time to catch HUGH and El just a few feet away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Their little dog, MADISON slips out between BARB‚Äôs feet and yips at HUGH and El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Little rat!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BARB</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh, look who it is! El, sweetheart, how‚Äôd he rope you into helping him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to HUGH)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And don‚Äôt call my baby a rat. I hope you bought some liverwurst.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You think I want to hear your mouth? Of course, I bought liverwurst.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You told them nice and thick right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yeah, I told them thick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Did you hold up two fingers like I told you to do? Hold up two fingers, though yours are much fatter, and show them how thick?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH doesn‚Äôt answer BARB. He gives her a look.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB moves out of the way of the door to let both HUGH and El into the apartment, and as they walk into the kitchen to drop off the groceries:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb (CONT‚ÄôD)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Who‚Äôd you get cut the meat? Was it the slob Marianne? Or was it the sweet colored boy Danny?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Danny.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to El)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Danny is such a sweet boy. Light skinned too. Probably got some white in him, I bet. I always said: blacks need some white in them to ease those large features. He also knows just how I like my liverwurst.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El kneels to the floor to play with MADISON.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El wraps the dog in her arms and nuzzles MADISON‚Äôs nose. This silences the dog‚Äôs yapping.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Aw, my little sweetie loves you, El. She never calms down that easily, especially not with, old mister grumpy pants.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El swings her backpack onto the front of her body, reaches in, and pulls out a notepad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She writes down a note to BARB.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BARB (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me talk it over with Hugh. But I couldn‚Äôt see why not. How could we say no to such a sweet girl?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El smiles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. apartment complex - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hangs a poster on the apartment complex BULLETIN BOARD.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GUS, an older mustachioed sleazeball, and manager of the apartment complex, escorts a young couple, ENRIQUE and NIKOLENA, both don a pair of shades and an itch they can‚Äôt scratch.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The trios conversation is heard out of the frame before they enter the frame and then pass El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Gus</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>If you don‚Äôt like the lot we just looked at, and you have some patience‚Ä¶we‚Äôre going to be having some tenants moving out sooner then they might be expecting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Enrique</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Looks like someone is up shit‚Äôs creek.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Gus</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And there ain‚Äôt no paddle shop midway down this river, brothah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Nikolena</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>How is‚Ä¶like, the crime around here?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The trio passes El‚Äôs backside, she turns and looks towards GUS.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Gus</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Crime is like nonexistant, sistah. It‚Äôs a real family environment, get me? We‚Äôre all hard workers around here. All keep our noses down and out of each other‚Äôs business. Julian, the guy who owns this place don‚Äôt take no shit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GUS SNIFFLES and WIPES his NOSE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GUS turns to look back at El, El looks away. GUS looks over El, checking her out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ENRIQUE catches GUS‚Äô glance.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Enrique</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Is that legal around these parts?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Gus</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What‚Äôs legal nowadays?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Enrique</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Old enough to pee, old enough for me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>NIKOLENA CACKLES. GUS and ENRIQUE FIST BUMP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ext. Sheen‚Äôs Apartment - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El stands outside of Sheen‚Äôs apartment. Sheen‚Äôs APARTMENT DOOR FRAMES El‚Äôs smaller frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / living room - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen lazes on the couch, scantily clad smoking a cigarette. Dave walks into the frame, holding a big wrench.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I fixed your toilet. Whoever said there aint no one whose shit don‚Äôt stink‚Ä¶</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>‚Ä¶thanks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I‚Äôm pathetic and need to go out of town for a thing I don‚Äôt care about because my wife owns me. Watch our retarded daughter, please? We can‚Äôt pay you anything because we don‚Äôt have any money.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave laughs, then cries, crumpling to the ground he crawls over to Sheen and licks her toes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. Sheen‚Äôs apartment - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hesitates knocking on the door, she raises her hand to knock, lowers it then walks out of frame, only before returning into frame, raises her hand once more and then finally knocks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El fidgets awaiting Sheen‚Äôs arrival.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / work space - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen, with one hand, shoots spray-paint onto a canvas, with the other she smokes a fat blunt.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen hears the knock of the door, casually takes another hit, stands up from her seated position, looks towards her air freshener and decides within an instant that it is not worth concerning herself with.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen moves her way through the apartment and reaches to answer the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ext. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / front door - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El quickly backs up as the front door to Sheen‚Äôs apartment swings open.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen leans against the frame of her doorway.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CAMERA CUTS between them, first framing them separately and then as they move closer to one another captures them both in one frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Right on time, just as your pops said.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El pulls out a card from her pocket, it reads: ‚Äúhello, can you give me your cellphone number, please?‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen‚Äôs dog burst from between her legs. Her dog is named ALBERT EINSTEIN, but Sheen calls her Albie for short.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie takes to El immediately as El drops to her knees and allows Albie to lick her face up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie, Albie, relax for christ‚Äôs sakes! Let off the girl. I‚Äôm</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>sorry, El. Your pops already gave me your cell number. Come on on inside.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El rushes through the door and enters her home at the guidance of Albie who circles her movements, and then guides her to the kitchen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What do they serve there at after school anyway: three day old pizza, sloppy who knows what meat, Jamaican beef pockets?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El unloads her backpack and its content onto Sheen‚Äôs table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúJamaican Beef Patties. I like those.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen looks to her phone, the text appears on the screen (similarly to subtitles (think ‚ÄúHouse of Cards‚Äù)).</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Patties, pockets. Don‚Äôt be pedantic. Pedantic is lame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El smiles at this sentiment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Then sends short rapid fire texts: ‚ÄúI am hungry, if you don‚Äôt mind. And, I‚Äôm not picky at all. Whatever you have I‚Äôll eat. I know how to cook too: tuna salad, Mac n cheese.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I have an idea. Since this is gonna be a two night affair, why don‚Äôt you get your homework out of the way first, plant your behind on that table, do your schoolwork and then we have the next day and a half free to relax and do what we want. Does that sound fair?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El nods her head approvingly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And in the meantime, I will make you and me some delicious Mac n cheese. But I will warn you that</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>once you try my ultra special mega spectacular Mac n cheese you will never be able to taste that Kraft shit the same ever again without coming knocking on my door for the real stuff.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El laughs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Girl, I‚Äôm not kidding you. This is like some super secretive samurai shit passed on down from my great grandma down to my grammy (skipping my mom because she was ungrateful, according to grammy), and fell down right onto me right before my grammy died. She used to make it for me when my mom used to leave me at her house all the time. This Mac n cheese will change your damn life, girl. Trust. Anyway, you make like a plant, finish your school work and then us girls will spend time doing whatever the hell we want. You like scary movies?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúNot really‚Ä¶But I could try.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We‚Äôll figure something out. Your choice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen leaves El to her work. While time elapses in hyper speed, we see that El gets out some textbooks and does her homework. Sheen in the foreground makes food, smokes cigarettes, and texts on her cellphone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>At one point during this time elapse, Sheen‚Äôs mouth moves sending some data El‚Äôs way, and Sheen leaves frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Time slows down.CAMERA follows Sheen leaving the kitchen, Sheen leaves the apartment and closes the door behind her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CUT TO El sitting in the kitchen, suspicious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She quickly turns around to the window covered in blinds, and peaks through the blinds to spy Sheen getting in a YELLOW CORVETTE, only for a moment before quickly getting back out and heading back towards her apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El quickly turns around back to her schoolwork and pretends as though nothing has occurred as Sheen walks back into the apartment and resumes her position at the stove stirring the Mac n Cheese.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Some time elapses.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hope you‚Äôre hungry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El looks up in approval.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen preps a bowl of her mind blowing Mac n Cheese, places it at the table in front of El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Your tastebuds await heavenly bliss.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen hovers, waiting for El to take a bite, which in time El does. El quickly shows a sign of praise.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Well? What do you think?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúNever Kraft again.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen offers El a high five, and El accepts.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen turns her back to El to make herself her own bowl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie appears from below the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El quickly hands over a spoonful of Mac n Cheese to Albie and Albie lingers for another.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El spoon feeds Albie one more bite, then raises a finger to her mouth, shushing the dog.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen returns to the table with her own plate of food.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen stands behind El, and she snaps a selfie of them together eating her self proclaimed famous Mac n Cheese.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen sits at the table, and plays around with her food, while El finishes her bowl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen takes her and El‚Äôs bowl, without ever taking a bite, and places it onto the counter before leaving the frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / bedroom - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen is crouched on her floor, lotus position, sitting next to her bedside table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen reaches into her bra, pulls out a baggie of three Percocet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen grabs one, puts it into a one dollar bill, and using a lighter from the bedside table crushes the pill into a powder form. She pushes the powder onto her bedside table from the surface of the bill, cuts the powder into lines, rolls the bill and then snorts it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El helps herself to a second helping of food.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sits at the kitchen table alone, eating a bowl of pasta by herself. She finished the bowl, and brings it to the kitchen sink, rinses the bowl, and places it in the dishwasher.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen walks in from off screen, a little bouncy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Oh, you didn‚Äôt need to do that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El nods that it is no trouble at all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>In the middle of the kitchen table sits a fruit bowl but without any fruit, in the bowl is an array of polaroids. Most of them are black, maybe there‚Äôs the outline of a face or a hand, but for the most part they are all poorly lit and dim.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El reaches into the bowl and starts looking at them more closely.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT‚ÄôD)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Those are all the rejects.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El looks up to Sheen, her face poses a question.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Let‚Äôs just say that when I have a polaroid camera in one hand, and a drink in another, I don‚Äôt take the best pictures. Some come out cool. Some are shit. My friend Nat, is always trying to hide my camera when she comes over cause she says I‚Äôm such a waste. Polaroids are expensive.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen watches El as she makes her way back to her work and packs up her homework.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen draws closer to the table without El realizing, and she sees the open pages of El‚Äôs notebook.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON El‚Äôs NOTEBOOK which is filled with sketches and drawing, people Sheen might recognize, the neighborhood, local stores, et cetera.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON a drawing of HUGH.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON a specific SKETCH of Sheen COOKING.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Girl, you can draw? I don‚Äôt know why I‚Äôm asking. Girl, you can draw. God damn. How long you‚Äôve been drawing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>On her notepad, El writes: ‚ÄúSince I can remember.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen grabs El‚Äôs notebook, and skims through the pages.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / workspace - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El enters Sheen‚Äôs workspace.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The entire perimeter of the room (the room parallels where El‚Äôs bedroom would be in her own house) is covered in canvas that is painted in graffiti art.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El is astounded by Sheen‚Äôs work.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El spins around taking in all of the artwork, Albie spins around her, and Sheen watches from the doorway, taking it all in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The joy unfolds for a few beats before we move on to another close up of Sheen who smiles foggily.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>If you like this, I have to take you to Wynwood some day soon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El turns to Sheen with a confused look.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen looks up Wynwood on her iPhone and shows El photos.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>An art district down in Miami. We can ride the tri-rail down there. With your parents‚Äô permission of course. I think you‚Äôd be super into it. I‚Äôll be on one of those walls one day soon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / bedroom - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen is next to her bedside again, continuing the process from before. This time, however, more sloppily.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen reaches into her pocket counts cash, and then searches for her cellphone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / workspace - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El works on a blank canvas with spray paint. She paints with bright primary colors. Albie sits at her heels.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ext. Apartment complex - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen saunters down a set of stairs and gets into the same YELLOW CORVETTE. The CAMERA lingers on the car, its tinted windows don‚Äôt allow us to look in, and then Sheen gets out and walks towards the CAMERA.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El eats a bowl of cereal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen looks over different nail polishes at the kitchen table. Sheen is in pajamas, lax, braless. There is an air of comfort between them that has grown more palpable.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúNot hungry?‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Nope, I‚Äôm never hungry for breakfast. I am hungry to hear your opinion on what color I should paint our nails though.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúPurple. Matches your hair.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Imma do purple, with some specks of black. A purple fierce cheetah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(she does a cat claw scratch)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Rawr! You want purple too? Or you want to pick your own color.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúNever painted my nails. Sandra never took me.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That‚Äôs okay, cause I been painting my nails since I was six, so consider me a goddamn professional. Now pick a color and I‚Äôll make you fly as fuck.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El gestures towards a color.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / workspace - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CANVAS‚Äô POV</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sheen works on some of her art. In the foreground, El sits on the floor with some of her own work in front of her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El stops for a moment, pets Albie, and instead of working on her own work, she watches Sheen working in her element.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs car - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen is behind the wheel, smoking a cigarette with her window rolled down. El is staring out the window with a reserved smile. Music plays on the radio, Sheen sings along.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You‚Äôre not gonna make me pick an ice cream flavor for you too, are you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El‚Äôs cellphone begins to ping and at first Sheen ignores the incoming messages, until it becomes a barrage of messages.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El reaches into her pocket, pulls out her cellphone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Awfully popular this afternoon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El rolls her eyes and sticks her phone back in her pocket.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Everything alright. Boy trouble? Bet boys love you. Boys are always telling me to shut my mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúBitches from school. Annoying.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Let me tell you something about bitches: they ain‚Äôt gonna grow, they ain‚Äôt gonna change, maybe they‚Äôll get pregnant, maybe they‚Äôll marry the same guys they‚Äôve been fucking since they were 16. They‚Äôre going nowhere and nowhere fast, sweetie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El smiles at this insight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>So keep your chin up, and remember that whoever high school is hardest for ends up on the other end thriving. I got knocked around by some bitches in high school cause they had nice new Jordans and I had Payless shoes and Walmart shirts. And now look at me, I‚Äôm cool, right? Oh, god, I never thought I‚Äôd ask if I was cool. I‚Äôm getting old, aren‚Äôt I? Fuck, now I sound like my dad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / living room - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sits on the floor in the living room, the television on, and El catches up on some correspondence with her blog followers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Silhouettes of Sheen and their neighbor JEANNIE are framed by the window. JEANNIE is a middle aged woman, on her second marriage to a much younger man, WALTER. JEANNIE‚Äôs first husband committed suicide in their basement after 9/11.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>At first, El pays no mind, but when their voices raise El is distracted and then MUTES the television to hear what they are saying.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>JEANNIE (O.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If we keep seeing all these random shades walking up and down our halls, I‚Äôm going to report you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (O.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Oh, are you, bitch?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>jeannie (O.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yes, I most certainly will. And believe me, bitch, I‚Äôm not the only one who notices all the comings and goings from your front door. Having trouble making rent?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (O.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>No, I‚Äôm fucking not. Fuck, why am I even answering, you‚Äôre not my goddamn mom. How I make rent is none of your business.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Jeannie (O.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Watch your tone, young lady‚Ä¶you don‚Äôt want to fuck with me, I‚Äôm from New York and I fight fucking dirty, cunt.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment/bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Sheen are laying on Sheen‚Äôs bed, they are close. A light from a film plays across their face. El is wide awake, absorbing. Sheen is barely awake, but contented. We linger here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen slowly falls entirely asleep.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It takes awhile for El to notice, but after sometime her eyes dart to Sheen checking on her, she notices her asleep.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El slowly and carefully maneuvers to unleash a blanket from somewhere off screen, then covers Sheen‚Äôs sleeping body.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dissolve to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. Sheen‚Äôs apartment - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Sheen stand just outside of Sheen‚Äôs apartment door. El is packed up and is on the way out to head back home.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She kneels down to say goodbye to Albie, then stands again to meet Sheen at eye level.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It was fun, chick! We need to do it again, and don‚Äôt feel like your parents need to be out of town for us to spend time together. It‚Äôs fun working with another super talented girl. Us girls will rule the world one day. You can bet your bottom dollar. And oh, almost forgot‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen darts back inside, and returns quickly with a key ring. She sorts through her keys and hands El a key.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Okay, here‚Äôs the rules: I‚Äôm trusting you with this key, so please just text me before you come over. At night and on the</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>weekends I usually won‚Äôt be here, and I can‚Äôt really look at my phone when I‚Äôm behind the bar, so if I don‚Äôt answer and you need to pick up Albie, no worries.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Sheen embrace.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen holds on for a little bit longer than El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen goes back inside and closes the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El starts off towards her apartment, turns back towards Sheen‚Äôs to sneak a goodbye peek and sees that Albie is poking his nose through the blinds to spy her leaving.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie barks a few times and El smiles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
