    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INT. Sheen‚Äôs APARTMENT / BEDROOM - EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El denies another dog walking customer. She scrolls through some photos of her being photographed with a customer‚Äôs dog, citing her as the best dog walker.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. GARY‚ÄôS APARTMENT - EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GARY, 40‚Äôs, construction worker, asks El how much it cost to feed his dog in the morning‚Äôs before she heads to school.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 7/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BARB"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HUGH"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. DOG PARK - EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El fights her way through multiple gate barriers with all the dogs in tow trying to make her way into the dog park. She plays fetch. Tries to break up a dog fight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INT./ext. MULTIPLE LOCATIONS - Different times</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El collects her pay from her clients, quick cutting from client to client.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Barb and Hugh‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB stands by the stove, casually stirring some food. HUGH sit at the kitchen table, in his undershorts, smoking a cigarette.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I hear the damned mutt yapping. He‚Äôs close. You better go let her in and let the girl know you ain‚Äôt paying her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I‚Äôm not the one not paying her. You are. So you better go tell the girl that we can‚Äôt pay her this week.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I‚Äôm not telling the girl a god damned thing. You wanted her to take care of the mutt, you go and tell her. I‚Äôm not embarrassing myself. I still have some dignity, you know. This old fart still‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Has some god damned dignity. I know. And the mutt has a name, you old grouch. And if you‚Äôd be nice to Madison, she wouldn‚Äôt be walking around in a terror all day that you‚Äôre gonna beat the poor thing till it pisses on the floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tell that thing if if stays out of my way, I‚Äôll stay out of its and everything will be a whole lot more peaceful around here, you hear?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>There‚Äôs a knock at the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH peaks out from the blinds.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And she got the druggie‚Äôs dog in tow too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Go put some pants on, you slob. I‚Äôm inviting that sweet girl in for some food at least. No more smoking in the kitchen. Go, go, hurry now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB walks over to the table to shoo HUGH and waves her arm in the air to shoo the cloud of smoke from the recently put out cigarette.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>EXT. BARB and HUGH‚Äôs apartment - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El is in front of BARB and HUGH‚Äôs apartment. She has Albie and MADISON in tow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB opens the front door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BARB</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sweetie, sweetie, thank you for delivering our little girl. Hope she was well behaved.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El nods.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Please come in for some dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El signals towards Albie. Its clear that she‚Äôd rather not, but that subtlety is lost on BARB.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Don‚Äôt worry, you could bring Albie in. Please, come in, we insist.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hesitates.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB reaches out and grabs El shoulder to usher her into the apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB closes the front door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El lets Albie go and he goes barreling into their apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and BARB linger by the front door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Here‚Äôs the story, sweetie:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(in a hushed voice)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>we actually can‚Äôt afford to pay you this week, Hugh is waiting on‚Ä¶</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(whispers)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>the check.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(raises her voice a bit more)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>So please consider this a down payment on how well you‚Äôve been treating our baby. She hasn‚Äôt been this lively since she was a tiny puppy. And god knows, she hasn‚Äôt smelled this nice since ever.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB ushers El along to the kitchen. HUGH has returned to his post, he is reading the newspaper, glasses on the bridge of his nose, squinting. He doesn‚Äôt acknowledge their entrance into the kitchen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ROUND OF APPLAUSE as El walks into the kitchen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El smiles at the CAMERA and waves.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Honey, El is going to join us for dinner. She said the food smelt so good, she couldn‚Äôt resist. Don‚Äôt be rude, Hugh, say hello.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HUGH</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello, dear. How‚Äôs school?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH asks his question, quickly returning the paper to blocking his face from the rest of them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="36" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>CANNED LAUGHTER.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh, tell El how sweet our puppy has been, how much energy she has had since she started walking her a few weeks ago.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yeah. Sweet. Very sweet. Energy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MADISON yips at HUGH‚Äôs feet. HUGH without thought begins to beat the dog with the paper he has in his hands.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="37" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>CANNED LAUGHTER.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Honey, take a seat. Make yourself at home. Dinner will be ready soon.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hugh</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Better be. Or I‚Äôll knock you the fuck out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to El)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ask my first wife.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="37" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>CANNED LAUGHTER.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Barb</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Oh hush.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>HUGH shoots BARB a glance.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BARB shivers in the corner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="16 6/8" Page="37" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ALANI"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>CANNED LAUGHTER.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra is putting together a lesson plan for her class on the kitchen table, she takes a moment to sort through some of her student‚Äôs papers. Dave stands by the stove tending to dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Eh, screw it. Move on. You don‚Äôt get paid enough to care. You know me, work only as hard as you‚Äôre paid.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Maybe that‚Äôs why you got ‚Äòlet go,‚Äô Dave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>For fuck‚Äôs sake, Sandra, I got let go because no one can afford to put in any fucking windows in this neighborhood, let alone a hundred mile radius. Home Depot took all the work from Stan so then Stan had to cut people‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave, I heard this before. It‚Äôs been 2 months since Home Depot, or Stan, or whoever, ruined your life. Move on or move out. Maybe your black cloud will follow you and keep its rain off of me cause I‚Äôm honestly sick of getting wet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sure, Sandra. Whatever you say. Here try this pasta.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave walks over to the table, blowing cool through pursed lips a noodle on a ladle before offering it to Sandra.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (cont‚Äôd)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A little more?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Leave it on for another minute or so. I like it a‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Softer, I know. After this I gotta go to the college kids‚Äô apartment. Those little bastards better tip.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Kids don‚Äôt know what tipping is. They especially don‚Äôt tip old men.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El will. At least I hope she will know to have some respect. You know, there‚Äôs nothing more important than respect in this world.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sure, Dave. Where is El?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave walks over the fridge.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON a laminated spreadsheet with El‚Äôs dog walking schedule on it, Dave‚Äôs finger finds the right day and hour.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She should‚Äôve been home forty five minutes ago.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>For the first time this entire conversation, Sandra looks up from her work.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That girl is never late.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She‚Äôs fine. She‚Äôs always been fine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ext. Apartment complex - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie walk towards Sheen‚Äôs apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El stops and drops to a knee to search for Sheen‚Äôs key in her backpack.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Police lights suddenly spark and beat against the apartment structure and across El and Albie‚Äôs face and body.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie notices immediately, El takes a second before she lifts her head towards the assault of lights.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El slowly stands backup, and her and Albie continue towards Sheen‚Äôs apartment hesitantly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>TWO POLICE OFFICERS walk up a flight of stairs and head in the same direction, the OFFICERS and El and Albie both walk from a distance towards each other.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They beat El and Albie to Sheen‚Äôs front door, which causes El to stutteringly back away from her destination as the OFFICER‚Äôs knock on the door a handful of times.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We track El and Albie‚Äôs movements as she doubles back and down a flight of stairs to watch from some shrubbery that obscures her and Albie from sight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A couple of rounds of knocks followed by more and more aggressive shouting plays out before the OFFICERS barge their way into Sheen‚Äôs apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Another handful of police cars arrive, along with an ambulance, and a fire truck.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El receives a text from Dave: ‚ÄúAre you almost home, dinner is getting cold? We talked about this. Mom says when dinner is cleaned up the kitchen is closed.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie linger, before‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El books it with Albie from her hiding place up a flight of stairs and towards her apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. El‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra removes the places at the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave scrubs dishes at the kitchen sink.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El bursts in, clearly distraught.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What‚Äôs the hold up, El? Why is that dog with you? If you‚Äôre going to be out this late, we don‚Äôt know if this is the best idea for you doing this dog walking business. Little girls should not be out past dark. We can‚Äôt see your grades go down. And we‚Äôre a family. We eat together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You know the rules.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We spoke about this. You need to set boundaries with these peoples. Cash up front, strict timelines, no dinners instead of pay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El types into her cellphone, sending them a group message: ‚ÄúSheen‚Äôs in trouble. Cops are outside of her apartment.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave and Sandra‚Äôs cells ping.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hands are wet. Can you read it out loud.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She says that Sheen‚Äôs in trouble. There are cops outside her place. Who is Sheen again?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The girl whose apartment I worked in a few weeks ago, broken shower head‚ÄîEl stayed at her place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra stares into Dave‚Äôs soul.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The police are outside the girl‚Äôs house who you, Dave, had babysit our girl? The girl you vouched for, the girl you said seems like a stand up citizen of our neighborhood.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>For all you know it could be a parking summons.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>For all you know it could be a Russian spy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Typical for you to jump to that conclusion. All I saw was a girl who was a painter who might‚Äôve related to another girl who was a painter. Typical for you to judge that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El flustered by the conversation turning from her concerns into a shouting match, texts: ‚ÄúCan someone go find out what is happening?‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Read it to me again, Sandra.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra places a stack of plates next to the sink, and walking out of the room, says:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Read it yourself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave wipes his hands and reads the text message.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El stares at him, waiting for his response, eyes watering. The sirens beat in through the slits in the blinds.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, I wouldn‚Äôt worry yourself about this. Don‚Äôt be like your mother, worst case isn‚Äôt always the case.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúSandra is not my mother.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie exit the room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave is left standing in the kitchen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CAMERA tracks him leaving the apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. El‚Äôs apartment / El‚Äôs bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sits on her bed, her knees in her chest, she‚Äôs staring directly at the CAMERA. Albie is perched next to her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El waits for the sirens and the chaos to die down.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>O.S. we hear the front door slam closed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave fumbles around the apartment, washes his hands, heads down the hallway, and knocks on El‚Äôs bedroom door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El stands from her seated position and moves to open the door a crack for Dave to see a part of her face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Can I come in?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El doesn‚Äôt open the door any further for him to enter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Okay. It‚Äôs not good. She‚Äôs dead. Her dog can stay for a few nights, but you need to find him a new home. I‚Äôm allergic, I told you that right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El closes the door on Dave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Walks over to the bed, and then slumps over and onto it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie sensing El‚Äôs despair hops up onto the bed and begins nuzzling and licking her face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El wraps Albie in an embrace.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>O.S. we can hear the muffled arguing of Sandra and Dave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / Sandra and Dave‚Äôs bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave sits naked, knees to chest in the corner, whimpering.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra, donning leather, imposes from the bed, on all fours, screaming, and wagging her finger down to Dave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Blah, blah, blah, blah, I‚Äôm pathetic, I‚Äôm a loser.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You killed her, didn‚Äôt ya? Spineless. You always wanted to fuck her, fuck anything that walks. Couldn‚Äôt control yourself?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Fucked her then killed her to clean up your pathetic little mess.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / El‚Äôs bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sets an alarm on her phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie embrace each other as time speeds up, El and Albie both fall in and and out of sleep, and after some time the sirens from outside die down and the room becomes pitch black.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El‚Äôs phone lights up and her alarm blares for a moment, both her and Albie jump awake in the darkened bedroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El turns the lights on, and suits up. She slips socks onto Albie‚Äôs feet so his nails don‚Äôt pitter patter as they sneak out of the apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CAMERA tracks behind El and Albie as they sneak through the hall towards Sandra and Dave‚Äôs room. The television is blasting, which seems to be a good sign as she continues on her trek.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She tracks the hallway, being quiet and careful, Albie follows closely at her feet‚Äîif she pauses for a moment, so does Albie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El carefully opens the front door, slips her and Albie out through it, then closes it with the doorknob pre-turned so it doesn‚Äôt make any sound as it‚Äôs closed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She locks the door behind her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. Apartment complex - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie move through the complex sticking to the shadows and avoiding the moonlight‚ÄîEl knows that there are eyes everywhere in the neighborhood.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie arrive at Sheen‚Äôs front door. Crime scene tape covers the frame of the door. For a moment, El searches for her key, but Albie pushes in with his nose through the front door as the lock‚Äôs been busted by the forceful entry of the police.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, shocked, quickly follows inside, she slips underneath the crime scene tape careful not to disturb it then closes the door behind her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>LONG TAKE: The CAMERA follows El and Albie as they track their way through the apartment quickly and efficiently.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Nothing is out of place. Everything is in order.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El takes a moment to feed Albie, who has been lapping up water in the background.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>When they get to the bedroom, CLOSE ON their silhouettes on the closed bedroom door, then as the door swings open, CLOSE ON a disturbed and disrupted bed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, equipped with cellphone (not emotions), starts snapping pictures of everything she sees around her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She snaps photos of the bed, and finds some speckles of blood stained into the sheets.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She takes pictures of the bedside tables which have some drug baggies, tobacco, faint traces of powder, and provocative polaroids.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Stay CLOSE ON the disheveled bedside table as El exits the frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / workspace - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El heads down the hallways and into the WORKSPACE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She takes snaps of all Sheen‚Äôs artwork. Albie enters the frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON a piece of artwork that portrays violence and rape, yet also seems seductive and powerful.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El moves towards the kitchen, and she notices a bunch of polaroids are posted and splayed all along the refrigerator. The polaroids contain a random splattering of young adults and some other random strange individuals.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El makes a digital snapshot of all of them before disturbing any of them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>FLASH Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The PARTIES depicted in the photos meld all into one PARTY, coming alive ‚Äî the only just empty apartment, now filled with drunken partiers. El is able to move through the party as if she was there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El looks around the smoke filled apartment, music blasting, Sheen‚Äôs jumping up and down, camera in hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The front door opens, Sheen yells at the entrance of a new visitor, walks up to him/her and starts to make out with them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We‚Äôve been waiting for you, motherfucker!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El at first disturbed, then moves on into the other parts of the apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>In the living room, a group of kids are playing a card game and passing around two nice and thick blunts.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>One of the partiers, sitting a bit distant from the others in a love seat crushes up some narcotics and sniffs it before offering the drugs to a buddy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GARY enters from the hallway into the party, sticking out like a sore thumb as an older middle aged man surrounded by younger people, his style is off from the rest of the party, he‚Äôs bald or balding‚ÄîEl immediately spots him and notes the creepy appearance of the 40+ year old at a 20 year old‚Äôs house party.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GARY takes a seat next to one of the younger woman and instantly begins to manhandle her, placing his hands all over her. She is drunken and resistant, but gives into his forcefulness. GARY grabs her breast and shoves his hand down her pants. The crowd cheers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SAL enters moments after the last entrance of the last visitor. SAL wears a yellow biker outfit, similarly to the outfit we‚Äôve seen in the first few moments of the film.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SAL and Sheen embrace, they look comfortable with one another. There is an exchange of cash between the two of them that is obvious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen leads SAL into the hallway and into her bedroom. El pauses then follows them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hesitates outside of the doorway, she hears no discernible sound. She tries to open the door, but the door will not budge.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GARY comes rushing down the hallway.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El falls to the floor as GARY‚Äôs immense force knocks the wind out of her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GARY bangs and knocks on Sheen‚Äôs door, yelling and hollering.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CUT BACK TO El ALONE IN THE KITCHEN standing in front of the fridge.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>This level of intimacy between all the patrons of the party spurs El to notice a pattern in the photos.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Once El notices that Sheen seems to intimately posed with more than just SAL, with both man and woman alike. We quickly see a photo of Sheen lip locked with a female, the top of their faces cut off by the frame of the polaroid.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Using the reference photo she took before disturbing the pictures, she rearranges all the photos she disturbed in her digital documentation of the analogue polaroids.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / El‚Äôs bedroom - early morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie lay under the blankets of El‚Äôs bed. El has her laptop opened, while her cellphone uploads all the photos onto her desktop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She collects all the files on her desktop into a folder called: ‚ÄúEvidence.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A knock at the door disturbs her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El lowers the light on her screen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie gets excited, El hushes him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Time to wake up sweetie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El peeks out from underneath the covers to spy that it is day already. Simultaneously, her alarm goes off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She hops out of bed and over to her window, and watches the parking lot down below. She notices that GARY‚Äôs truck isn‚Äôt in the parking lot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Gary‚Äôs truck - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON both of GARY‚Äôs large hands gripping the wheel, he‚Äôs burning rubber, pedal to the metal on a dark and long highway. SLOWLY PULL BACK to REVEAL GARY, paranoid as all Hell, checking around, neck tweaking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON GARY‚Äôs reflection in the rear view mirror, his eyes jut to the right. PAN to a bloodied rope and knife lying in the driver‚Äôs seat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SIRENS appear in his rear view mirror.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>GARY‚Äôs eyes jerk back to the rear view mirror. He starts to bang a hand violently against the wheel, and then silently cry and whimper.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El is gobbling down cereal, her laptop propped in front of her, and she is laser focused. She is uploading a batch of photos to her blog‚Ä¶</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>‚Ä¶and writing a post asking her followers for help making connections between all of the evidence she has collected. She doesn‚Äôt post it right away, instead she spends time deciding on the right phrasing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave enters and El closes her laptop, and takes the rest of the cereal into her mouth by lifting the bowl and swishing the remains with big gulps to hurry out of the kitchen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave notices Albie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Oh, yeah, the dog. El, make sure you‚Äôre proactive in finding a home for him. He can stay a few nights but that‚Äôs it. Sandra is allergic and I think I might be too, honestly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sends Albie a look that he doesn‚Äôt have to go anywhere, she is going to take care of him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The landlord is kicking me some extra money to clean out Sheen‚Äôs apartment. I‚Äôll save some of the dog toys and bring them over here while you‚Äôre in school. Speaking of which, you think we can chain this dog up outside while you‚Äôre gone?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El grabs her cellphone to text Dave, Dave preemptively reaches for his cellphone to await her response.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El writes: ‚ÄúToo hot out today. He is an inside dog.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hesitates, then sends this next: ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt the police need to find the killer first before you throw away evidence?‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The officer says they‚Äôve seen this type of thing over and over again around here. Nothing was fishy. They seemed pretty sure, and we should just trust them‚Äîthey are the police after all, and they know way more about this then me or you. Believe me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El begins to tear up with anger. Her hands clench, her nails dig into the flesh of her palms.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave embraces El from behind as she is seated in the kitchen chair, then quickly leaves the kitchen to avoid any further awkward confrontation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>As soon as Dave exits the frame, El moves over to a kitchen drawer, opens it, and pulls out a photocopied list of all the tenants, their phone numbers, and their emails (where applicable).</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>O.S. we hear the sounds of someone drawing close.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Honey, are you in the kitchen?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El quickly snaps a photo, drops the paper back into the drawer, closes it, spins around and awaits the arrival of Sandra.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Her face shifts from determined to detrimental. She is playing them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Good morning. I‚Äôm about to head off to work. Please try and find a place to send the dog, he can stay a few nights, I wouldn‚Äôt mind having him, but Dave‚Äôs allergic.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra gives El a kiss on the cheek goodbye before leaving the kitchen and heading out the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Public transit / bus - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El parks herself in the same seat she was sitting in the last time we saw her on the bus.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El pulls up her photo of the photocopied contact list, finds the name of the two college kids listed on the sheet, TEDDY and SUSAN. The college kids apartment shares a wall with Sheen‚Äôs apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sends an email to them asking them when would be a good time for them to all meet. El pretends she is doing some type of social study project and needs their input on the project.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sends an email to JULIAN (previously mentioned by GUS as the owner of the APARTMENT COMPLEX) requesting the parking lot camera footage from the last few days.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El switches tasks, and begins to crop out all of the faces from the photos she collected, naming the ones she knows and leaving the faces she does not know unlabeled.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. Public school / playground - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>From the same familiar position we found El seated in during her high school recess at the beginning of the film, we find her in the same position once again. El has a penchant for sameness. Far from the festivities of high school lunch lazing, laptop on her lap, a set of earbuds firmly locked into her ears (the music she is listening to can be heard on screen), and munching on apple slices. This time she is drafting a questionnaire to hand out to her suspects and people of interest in her neighborhood.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON LAPTOP SCREEN as she begins to type the questions into a word processor. She spends time with the language of each question, sometimes backspacing and rewording, sometimes rapidly beating the words onto the screen with sureness.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The text below, as long with the questions, are read aloud by an amalgamation of the actors voices from the film. The voices shift and out from one another.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>‚ÄúI am conducting a series of interviews regarding the death of our neighbor. I have my suspicions that a murder has taken place right under our noses. Any information you can give me would really be helpful in serving justice.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What is your cellphone number? NOTE: Please read it nice and slowly so I have a moment to type it into my phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>May I record this for my records?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What is her name? (PICTURE of Sheen)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What‚Äôs your alibi for Wednesday night, December Twentieth, 2017?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Any suspects or persons of interest?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Have you noticed a yellow corvette visiting the parking lot anytime over the past week?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Impressions of Sheen as a member of our society.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Are there any other thoughts or facts that you would like to reveal to me regarding the incident? Anything you might like to add that I have not explicitly asked in this questionnaire?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Why should I not consider you a suspect?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El‚Äôs POV:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CAMERA PULLS BACK from the CLOSE UP of the computer SCREEN. The SCREEN is still in focus, but now we can see the blurred action surrounding El that she has been ignoring as she‚Äôs been locked into the task at hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CAMERA PULLS back even further until we are behind El‚Äôs shoulder.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>BLURRED SHAPES approach El from directly in front of her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The SCREEN of the laptop suddenly SLAMS CLOSED by a bracelet wearing, finger painted HAND that is revealed as the SCREEN shifts from OPEN to CLOSED in front of the CAMERA.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, at first distracted by her task, is caught off guard, her laptop slips to the concrete floor from the rough nature of the handling, ripping her earbuds from her ears (the music we heard previously is suddenly cut out), and makes an unfortunate CRACK as it hits the floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, still ignoring her surroundings, drops to the floor to inspect her computer. We can hear the drowned out sounds of dialogue from teenage girls beginning to take shape, however, this is all moving in slow motion. El lifts up her computer, spins around, placing it on the bench, opens the computer and it is restored to its last state before it fell, now with a CRACK running through the middle of the SCREEN. However, El has not lost any of her work.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CAMERA CUTS to a small crowd of teenage girls forming a circle around the bench that El kneels around. CAMERA spins around them, creating a claustrophobic net around El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The girls names are: MIA, EMILY, ALANI, ANDREA, and CHLOE. MIA is the ring leader.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don‚Äôt know what you‚Äôre worried about. Your piece of shit computer was already broken. That‚Äôs why you were ignoring us, right? The messages weren‚Äôt getting through to you, right? Right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Emily</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That seems to be the only explanation. Only logical one, anyhow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Andrea</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Unless she just all broken herself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Alani</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Doesn‚Äôt make sense that this bitch would ignore us. Us. We fucking royalty up in this motherfucker. ‚ÄòSpecially compared to her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Emily</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Well, this bitch is always on that stupid computer. Maybe it‚Äôs her only friend and she don‚Äôt want no real friends. Maybe she happy being all alone jerking off to chat bots.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>There is no doubt about that. Ain‚Äôt nothing scary on that screen that can‚Äôt get closed down when powered off. What you afraid of, dummy? Real life? My heel, bitch?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Andrea</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Nope no doubt you should be afraid of Mia‚Äôs heel. You don‚Äôt wanna make no other friends? You like having no friends?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>So you think when this group of bitches reaches out to this scrawny nasty bitch, she‚Äôd be dying to make friends with us. Real people. You scared of people? Your step dad fuck you when you were little?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Chloe</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia, maybe she ain‚Äôt just deaf and dumb, but blind too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ALANI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, maybe the bitch can‚Äôt read.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Is that true, bitch? You don‚Äôt know words?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Emily</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That would make sense. Yeah, maybe she don‚Äôt know how to write either. She‚Äôs probably retarded.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Probably? Definitely. And ungrateful to our attempt at charity.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El is still crouched on the ground, she allows the girls surrounding her to continue their berating of her, she allows them to keep their power, eyes to the floor, and quickly packing her backpack.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You would think this retarded bitch would be more than excited to wanna talk to us, right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Emily</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Retard!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Chloe</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Fucking retard! Look at us when we‚Äôre talking to you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Alani</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You don‚Äôt wanna be our friend?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Obviously, she don‚Äôt wanna be our friend. And even if she wanted to be our friend now, the invitation has officially been rescinded.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Andrea</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia was being nice and generous when she suggested we invite your simple ass to our group chat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to Emily)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sorta like when your brother Frankie helped out at the special olympics.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>emily</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to ANDREA)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>How is it at all like that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to El)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Generous as fuck, bitch. That is over with. Now you better watch yourself as you‚Äôre walking through the halls. You better watch how you looking at us. Yeah, keep your eyes down or we‚Äôll blind you, cunt. You ever see those videos online of those sand sluts getting acid in their face?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>chloe</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>My dad‚Äôs a plumber, we got acid in the garage.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MIA starts poking and prodding El as she is on the floor, who to this point has showed no sign of fear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We‚Äôd smash your face in now but‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Emily</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia can‚Äôt get no more strikes on her record.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MIA sends a sharp glance to EMILY.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El stands up suddenly and stares directly into MIA‚Äôs eyes, first with fire, then with a smile, then wraps her arms around her with a tight and overbearing hug, and then pushes right past her with speed and might and certainty.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON the group of girls as El hustles down the block and into the foreground of the frame, she turns, still with a big smile, and waves back to her antagonizers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The rest of the girls await MIA‚Äôs next move as they are all frozen by El‚Äôs display of warmth and affection at the crossroads of anger and spite.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That bitch is fucking crazy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MIA has an unlit cigarette in her mouth, she cocks her hand out and silently asks for one of the other girls to hand her a light. One of the others, instead of handing her a lighter, lights the cigarette in her mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Emily</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She don‚Äôt know who she is speaking to. We ain‚Äôt gonna let her get away with that disrespect.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MIA sends another sharp glance to EMILY.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The YELLOW CORVETTE pulls up behind the girls in the background.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Bakery - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="54" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>NO AUDIO. MUSIC TRACK.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHARON works behind the bakery counter. She tends to a short line of patrons. From behind the counter, we see through the bakery‚Äôs front glass windows El entering the frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. bakery - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="9 4/8" Page="54" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="JEANNIE"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>NO AUDIO. MUSIC TRACK CONTINUES.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El kills time outside of the bakery, hits the toes of her shoes against the cement sidewalk, walks in circles, does some jumps up and down, checks her phone. In the bakery, we can see SHARON finishing her duty to the patrons of the shop and the line shortens until no one is left in the bakery.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INT. Bakery - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Oh, it‚Äôs that time of the day already, huh? I never realize how much of the day has passed me by until your sweet face shows up and then I realize the whole day has just ran on by. Same as always?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El gestures that SHARON‚Äôs assumption is correct.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHARON moves around the counter to get El‚Äôs daily order. El drops to a knee, whips out her laptop, opens it, and places it onto the counter top.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The bread arrived a little late this morning, so the driver gave me an extra bundle of French twist. Give this to your mother, tell her Sharon says hello, you here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHARON hands over a bag of bread to El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Oh, what is this?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHARON sees the laptop opened. But she can‚Äôt read it as her eyes are bad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Is there something on here that you want me to read?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El gestures to the computer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Alright, alright, hold on. Let me get my reading glasses, sweetie. Hm, what is this? The screen is black, sweetie. And my, what a nasty crack you got running right down the middle. You should get that fixed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El reaches for the laptop, spins it around, moves the mouse to bring the computer back to life. She makes sure the questionnaire is the only thing on the screen that SHARON can see.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHARON begins to read the introduction to herself, she mouths the words, and sometimes says some of the words out loud. She arrives at the first question.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Okay, number A. Well, you already have my cellphone number, so moving right along.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHARON looks up from the screen and smiles at El. El returns a fired off forced smile of her own.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON SHARON as she tries and makes out the questions, she struggles to read the words on the screen. She speaks slowly, piecing the words together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Okay now, number B. Record me? Oh, my. I always hated the sound of my own voice. You ever call someone on the phone and get that feedback where you can hear your own voice, then ask yourself: jeez is that what I sound like? Ugh, what a nag. I‚Äôd rather you not record me. Okay, yeah, she‚Äôs the girl who lived next door. She lives next to that racket of a college dorm room. She‚Äôs a bit of a‚Ä¶um, whore, no? Sleeps around with the whole neighborhood. God bless her and paint an ‚ÄòA‚Äô on her forehead for the world to see and steer clear of. She comes in here a lot, but if it was my bakery we wouldn‚Äôt serve the likes of her. No, this neighborhood don‚Äôt need nothing like that. You ask me, someone like that gets what is coming to them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Church - dusk</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen lies tied up and splayed out on the altar, passed out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A CULT of HOODED FIGURES circle her body, chanting:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hooded figures</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Though She is not a virgin / He has never had no aversion / To feed His blood perversion.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen wakes from her drugged slumber, starts screaming and struggling.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>One of the HOODED FIGURES steps closer to the altar, pulls back the hood of the cloak, revealing SHARON. In SHARON‚Äôs hand she holds a swiveled dagger.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on DAGGER (HITCHCOCK PSYCHO KNIFE CLOSE UP).</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Bakery - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>STAY CLOSE ON El, her patience a virtue, as SHARON continues to answer, but takes many an aside to ramble and rant.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hm, last night? Well, I remember being home for Jeopardy, Family Feud, and Wheel. I got one of the Jeopardy questions right and was so excited I decided to treat myself to a helping of marble cake with a hefty scoop of fluff. And to be honest, I was going to have the cake regardless of whether I got the question right or not. This is all okay, of course, for my diabetes because it was low sugar and I haven‚Äôt had any cake in over a week. But no, I don‚Äôt really remember anything funny happening that night. I was eating my cake and then just heard all the hullabaloo happening down the way. That girl and those college kids were always bringing dark characters around the apartment. Anytime you see a cigarette butt you know who to attribute it to. Well, this is the reason I can‚Äôt wait to hit 55 so I can move to a retired community. So sick of the disrespect. I woke up one morning to a nice big old scratch across my car. One of those little bastards must‚Äôve just taken a key and scratched it for the fun of it. Who would scratch a poor old lady‚Äôs car? If it was up to me, I‚Äôd wring em up all by their necks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The sound of a bell is heard O.S., this is the sound of a customer coming into the bakery. A blurred shape enters the frame. CLOSE ON SHARON as she lifts the computer and hands it to El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hello, how can I help you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Customer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Three loaves of Italian bread, two plain, one seeded, please.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El begins to pack up her belongings.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sharon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to CUSTOMER)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Coming right up, sir.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>(to El)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Despite her unforgivable sins in the eyes of Heaven almighty, she was a beautiful girl. I have to say, though‚ÄîI really didn‚Äôt like those piercings or the tattoos. Especially the one on her breasts. A woman‚Äôs body should be cherished and unmarked, and covered. It just sends the wrong message. Now, don‚Äôt get me wrong, I‚Äôm a feminist. I even almost got arrested once at a protest at my campus. But I don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs right to scar God‚Äôs work. Let his creations die as they were born. Shame, a God darn awful shame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Fedex kinkos - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El is parked next to a printer in a Fedex Kinkos store. She edits some of the wording of the questionnaire she had created. Some hustle and bustle takes place around her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El looks up from her computer and off screen, giving an affirmative grin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A FEDEX EMPLOYEE enters the frame shortly thereafter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Fedex employee</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You ready to print?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El nods, spinning her laptop around.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Fedex employee</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>What size do you want these to be?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El writes on pen and paper: ‚Äú8.5in x 11in. Laminated, please. And I‚Äôd also like to print a 5 by 7 of this.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. fedex kinkos - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El exits the shop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El opens the package from Fedex. Checks the laminated cards.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on the LAMINATED QUESTIONNAIRE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on a PHOTOGRAPH of Sheen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. street - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El walks down the street.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A buses passes by her, pulls up a bit ahead of her, MICAH and TEDDY get off at the stop.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El caught up to them, but hangs back a bit‚Äîthey do not notice her as she tails them and listens in on their conversation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Micah</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You were wasted. Absolutely shitfaced hammered, man. So when I say it happened, it happened, and your opinion on the matter don‚Äôt really matter. I was the only sober-ish one. So trust a niggah when I say you missed some wild shit. Some life altering shit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Teddy</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I wasn‚Äôt wasted wasted. I remember the whole night, practically.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Micah</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Do you remember Alfie and Mary hooking up practically on top of your dead body?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Teddy</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>No.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Micah</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Or Antonio and Sara getting along, no fights, no beers flung across the room?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Teddy</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Micah</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That shit didn‚Äôt happen. How‚Äôd you get so fucked? Did you drink the pussy punch?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Teddy</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I don‚Äôt remember.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Micah</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Of course you did. Niggah, you don‚Äôt go to a frat party and drink the goddamn punch. That is the unspoken code between brothers that the drinks are for the sisters to knock their asses out. And you, silly bitch, got your bitch ass knocked out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Unknown kitchen - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A group of young men ‚Äî all dressed in collared polos emblazoned with large Greek letters on the front, shirts tucked into belted khaki shorts ‚Äî hover around a bubbling CAULDRON boiling and smoking. All of the men have a hand on a comically huge wooden spoon, stirring the cauldron.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A hooded figure emerges from the shadows with a vial. CLOSE on the text of the vial: ‚Äúfuck bitches‚Äù.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The hooded figure pours the vial into the cauldron.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>All the men smirk and then give each other high fives.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. College kid‚Äôs apartment - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A line of MEN walk down a hallway into different bedrooms, each of the MEN have a passed out GIRL slumped over their shoulders.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. apartment complex - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and the boys turn into their apartment complex. They turn one way, she turns another and then hustles home.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheen‚Äôs door is open, there‚Äôs a trash container in the courtyard, and Dave throws trash from the second floor right down into the trash container.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El hurries up the stairs and towards Sheen‚Äôs apartment. Dave throws down another bag of trash and spots El.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hey, honey. How was school? I got something for you. Wait here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave goes back into Sheen‚Äôs apartment. El overlooks the balcony and sees right down into the trash container. She notices a bunch of Sheen‚Äôs paintings have been tossed away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave manically rushes around Sheen‚Äôs apartment with rubber gloves on his hands, a spray bottle of cleaner in one hand, and a scrub brush in the other.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave enters Sheen‚Äôs art room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Women aren‚Äôt talented.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. Sheen‚Äôs apartment - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave comes back outside with a black bag.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Here you go. These are for the dog. They were the ones that hadn‚Äôt been torn to shreds yet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El takes the black bag, pulls out her cellphone, and texts Dave: ‚ÄúYou can‚Äôt throw away all this artwork. It just isn‚Äôt right.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave pats his pockets to find his phone, realizes he doesn‚Äôt have it, then walks inside to Sheen‚Äôs apartment once more. El follows behind him closely.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / living room - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Goddammit, where is my phone? This place is a disaster.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave finds his phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Honey, what else am I supposed to do with it? Give it to a museum? Museums usually ask artists for their art, not the other way around.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El texts: ‚ÄúThis is her life‚Äôs work.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Yeah, I‚Äôm sure it is. That‚Äôs why everything is so cheap in here. But she won‚Äôt be the only person whose life‚Äôs work will be forgotten, honey. All of the things we do one day no one will care about. Believe me you, or is it believe you me? Either way, I‚Äôm pretty much already forgotten. You think anyone gives a rat‚Äôs ass that I put in windows? And window‚Äôs are my life‚Äôs work. Now I clean out someone else‚Äôs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El rushes past Dave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment / workspace - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE ON one of the bigger pieces of art yet to be thrown away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El enters the frame, grabs it with both of her hands and leaves the frame.</Text>
