    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Sheen‚Äôs apartment - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on POLAROID on Sheen‚Äôs fridge, WALTER‚Äôs face in one of the photos.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Flash Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. High-rise apartment - unknown</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>JEANNIE, dressed in a trench coat, paces back and forth across a smoky Manhattan apartment. Light slips in through the slots of the drawn down window blinds.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>WALTER bursts in through the door, suitcases in hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They embrace and sloppily kiss, mashing their mouths together without opening their lips.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Jeannie</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You‚Äôre okay. You made sure from the right angle, right? You didn‚Äôt shoot him in the back of the goddamn head like some child?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Walter</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Gun in the mouth, like we practiced. I got the drugs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Jeannie</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Now we can run away together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Flash cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Jeannie‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Albie sniffs WALTER‚Äôs feet from under the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
