    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Julian</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>In my country, a little girl who can‚Äôt open her mouth like you would be worth a lot of money‚Ä¶ under one condition, you can still at least moan and moan loud. I bet you moan nice and good. If she could not moan or cry or scream or beg, she would‚Äôve been drowned by her mother and thrown into a hole to be forgotten. Or maybe burned.</Text>
