      <Text>Sal</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Get in. Leave your backpack and your phone on the street there. No tricks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SAL shows El that he has a pistol pointed right at her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El drops her bag onto the floor, places her cellphone into the backpack and pulls out a pen and pad before getting into the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Yellow corvette - afternoon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SAL and El sit across from one another in the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El has her hands on both knees, she is still.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>sal</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Keep nice and still, no sudden movements. Don‚Äôt want this gun to accidentally go off. I‚Äôve killed people before. My connect didn‚Äôt get his refill until the next day, so I was out of your girl‚Äôs favorite flavor, no reason for me to come over there. Your girl only called when she was trynna get high.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El quickly writes, bluffing: ‚ÄúAutopsy report says drugs. How‚Äôd she get them?‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sal</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Your girl sniffed 5 pills a day. You take away a feen‚Äôs high, they‚Äôll find something.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El writes: ‚ÄúDo you think she was killed?‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sal</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Don‚Äôt know. Don‚Äôt care. All I know is that it wasn‚Äôt me. Why would I kill the bitch that sucked my dick? Five dollars short and she‚Äôd swallow. Sometimes I‚Äôd pretend she was short.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra, Dave, and El eat dinner in silence. El hurries through her dinner, dumps her plate in the sink, and exits the kitchen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie lie in bed. El cuddles Albie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El opens Sheen‚Äôs blog account to find more followers to have come to her account as well as lots of likes on her posts.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El posts another one of Sheen‚Äôs pieces to her blog.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El receives a ping. It‚Äôs an email from JULIAN, he sent a link to a file with the past week‚Äôs worth of parking lot footage.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El rushes over to her desk, pulls up the footage and starts with the speed increased to see the last time GARY‚Äôs car was parked outside.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El finds the moment that GARY leaves and never returns. This time matches around the two days accounted for between her death and the police finding the body.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>ext. gary‚Äôs apartment - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on FRONT DOOR enshrined in shadows.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie enter the frame from the left.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El opens the door with Dave‚Äôs skeleton key.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Gary‚Äôs apartment / living room - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We watch as GARY‚Äôs apartment door swings open from inside. The door almost slams against the wall before El lunges forward and grabs the door before it makes a bang.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El and Albie hurry into the apartment. El shuts and locks the door behind them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>TWO CATS rush to the front door, meowing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El bends down to pet them while also petting Albie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The TWO CATS guide El to the closet, she opens the door, and then the TWO CATS lead her to the kitchen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Gary‚Äôs apartment / kitchen - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El pours food into their food bowls. El gives them each a fresh bowl of water.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. Gary‚Äôs apartment / bathroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El cleans out the cat litter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Gary‚Äôs apartment / kitchen</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El dumps the waste in the trash.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El walks over to the cats eating and lapping up water. El spends time with the cats and gives them love. She sits on the floor to pet them as they feed their starved bodies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. Gary‚Äôs apartment / bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El opens the bedside table drawers, first finds underwear, then finds an assortment of baggies, all with the same design.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El opens her cellphone, and using references photos, identifies that one bag in Sheen‚Äôs apartment matches all of these bags in GARY‚Äôs drawer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>int. El‚Äôs apartment / living room</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, Sandra, and Dave sit around the living room, mirroring the arrangement from the beginning of the film.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on El‚Äôs face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We know this has been tough on you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Really and truly very tough. Seems the job has been keeping you occupied, right? Some extra pocket change, at least.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>To be honest, I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôve ever seen you happier.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We told you how we were proud of you, right? You were really able to pick up some of the slack around here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Really impressive, sweetie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>In just six months you were able to turn it all around. We offered you a suggestion, and you took charge. Bravo to you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That‚Äôs not why we‚Äôre sitting you down though.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>No, unfortunately not.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We are so, so proud of you though.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Really and truly. But listen, this whole obsession‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>‚ÄîI wouldn‚Äôt necessarily call it an obsession.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>This whole‚Ä¶passion‚Ä¶of yours that you‚Äôve embarked on, this mission is nothing but a journey to fantasy land. It‚Äôs proving to effect your school life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Why have you been cutting school? Mr. Preston says you‚Äôve been leaving after lunch?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>You know we‚Äôre being as hard on you as we‚Äôd be on our own daughter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And we think of you like a daughter.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Of course. Of course, we do.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>But you need to understand, this new behavior will not stand. You can‚Äôt go hunting for answers to questions that don‚Äôt need asking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Questions a little girl like you should not even be musing about let alone asking around town about. I‚Äôve been getting all sorts of calls from all sorts of people.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It‚Äôs unhealthy for you, and we‚Äôre concerned. That‚Äôs all we‚Äôre saying: we‚Äôre concerned.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>And let me just go on record as saying this: while Sheen might‚Äôve seemed cool to you El, she might‚Äôve been more than what your young eyes could account for. I think it‚Äôs fair to call a spade a spade when the deck is dealt. Sheen‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>‚ÄîSheen‚Ä¶she killed herself. She took to many drugs and killed herself too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Like your parents. That‚Äôs what drug addicts do. Without fail. Their lives are dead ends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Like this wild goose chase.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Exactly, this whole conspiracy you are wrangling up is just that: a conspiracy. It will lead you nowhere, sweetie. You‚Äôre just a kid. So trust me, an older, wiser adult.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I used to think 9/11 was an inside job. Still doesn‚Äôt all add up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A psycho killed a school full of children in Connecticut. And conspiracy theorists thought it was a government scandal in order to take away guns. The conspiracy theorists wouldn‚Äôt allow the poor parents to grieve their kid‚Äôs deaths.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Your mom is saying‚Äî</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>I‚Äôm not her mom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra is saying that it‚Äôs time to grieve.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It‚Äôs okay to grieve, honey. Take this all as a learning experience.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra sends shade to Dave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra (cont‚Äôd)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Right, Dave? Maybe we don‚Äôt send our child to a crackhead‚Äôs house next time? Look what you‚Äôve done to this poor girl. First her mother, now this pathetic girl. Seems like you don‚Äôt want her to have any strong female role models in her life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sandra stands up and leaves the living room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Once Sandra is gone, Dave repositions himself and takes up more space in the frame.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dave</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Your </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">mom‚ÄîSandra‚Ä¶didn‚Äôt</Text>
      <Text> mean to get so hysterical. She just cares about you so much. Do you understand that? I hope that you can see that. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Here‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> the big picture, good news slash bad news, bad news first: we need you to give up on this whole Sheen thing, good news </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">we‚Äôll</Text>
      <Text> let you keep Albie. We can tell how much serenity </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">he‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> brought here for you. But you must swear to me‚Ä¶to us, no more inquiries, no more pestering the neighbors, no more leaving school early. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">You‚Äôre</Text>
      <Text> a kid, </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">it‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> time to act like one. This is not how we want you to be representing our family. And you are a part of our family now, whether you like it or not. And as this is my </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">house‚Äîmy</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">apartment‚Äîour</Text>
      <Text> apartment, what we say goes. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Let‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> also add to the record: </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">we‚ÄîI‚Äîlove</Text>
      <Text> you and just want you to succeed and not sink down the drain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on El smiling.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cut to:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Int. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">El‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> apartment / bedroom</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sits at her desk, her back to the camera. Albie lies on the floor under the desk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El checks </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Sheen‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> blog, which now has close to ten thousand followers. One of the recent photos El posted has gone viral.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El sees that the viral post has made its way to the front page of the internet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A ping fires off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El checks her email, Sheen has received an offer from art contractor in Miami regarding putting up one of her paintings in </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Wynwood</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El takes some time to absorb the information, and she smiles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El, with her voice for the very first time, reads the email out loud,</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dear Sheen‚Ä¶on behalf of the city of Miami and the district of </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Wynwood</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">we‚Äôd</Text>
      <Text> like to invite you to be a part of our 2018 catalogue. As you may know this a very prestigious honor. These art walls receive nearly one hundred thousand </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">artist‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> applications a year and will greatly add reverence and honor to your name. Please write back to us as soon as possible and let us know if you would be interested in participating in this great tradition. Your fan, the city of Miami.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>El types back: ‚ÄúThough the offer is a dream come true‚ÄîUnfortunately, I must decline. Thank you for the great and wonderful compliment just in the extension of the invitation.‚Äù</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CLOSE on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">El‚Äôs</Text>
      <Text> contented face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Fade to black.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
  </Content>

